title: Biscayne National Park: Reptiles
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Reptiles                Reptiles         The threatened American crocodile is frequently sighted along Biscayne's shorelines.   The following reptiles have been documented at Biscayne National Park. They are sorted alphabetically by common name. An asterisk denotes an exotic species. The list is not exhaustive, and documented sightings of species not on this list are welcome. Submit your sightings to the webmaster.
